# cf_ai_incident_response

> **Try the Agent here:** [https://incident-room.pages.dev](https://incident-room.pages.dev)

An AI-powered Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) agent that collaborates with users in real-time to diagnose and resolve infrastructure incidents. Built on the Cloudflare Developer Platform.

## ğŸš€ Live Demo
**[Insert your .pages.dev link here]**

## ğŸ› ï¸ Architecture
This project uses the "Edge-Native" stack to ensure low latency and stateful collaboration:
* **LLM:** `Llama 3.3` running on **Workers AI** for intelligent analysis.
* **Coordination:** **Cloudflare Workers** act as the entry point and router.
* **State & Memory:** **Durable Objects** maintain the chat history and the live "Defcon" status (Normal vs Critical) across all connected users.
* **Frontend:** A WebSocket-enabled UI hosted on **Cloudflare Pages**.

## âœ¨ Features
1.  **Real-time Chat:** Low-latency communication via WebSockets.
2.  **Agentic Capabilities:** The AI can autonomously trigger UI changes.
    * *Try it:* Tell the agent "The server is down!" and watch the dashboard turn red.
3.  **State Management:** The incident status persists in the Durable Object.

## ğŸ’» How to Run Locally

1.  **Clone the repository**
    ```bash
    git clone [https://github.com/Rana-Shumail/cf_ai_incident_response.git](https://github.com/Rana-Shumail/cf_ai_incident_response.git)
    cd cf_ai_incident_response
    ```

2.  **Install dependencies**
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```

3.  **Start the development server**
    ```bash
    npx wrangler dev
    ```
    The backend will start on `http://localhost:8787`.

4.  **Run the Frontend**

    Open `public/index.html` in your browser.
